DWELL

PURPOSE
Check numeric internal-state samples in CI.

Programs emit key=value lines. dwell checks them against contracts, emits plain
text events, and exits nonzero when an error contract fires.

dwell uses the same limit-rule input and event output shape as trip, so the same
key=value sample stream can be checked by either program for simple numeric
limits.

USAGE
cc -std=c99 -Wall -Wextra -O2 dwell.c -o dwell
./some_test_or_benchmark | ./dwell -r .dwell/contracts.dwell

CONTRACTS
Format:

key op number level event_id

Examples:

frame.ms              > 16.6    warn   frame.slow
queue.depth           > 1000    error  queue.backpressure
tokens.per_second     < 50      error  inference.too_slow
temperature           > 80      warn   temperature.high

Operators:

> >= < <= == !=

Levels:

info warn error

INPUT
Accepted forms:

frame.ms=18.7
queue.depth 1402

OUTPUT
Tab-separated events on stdout:

warn	frame.slow	frame.ms	>	16.600000000000001	18.699999999999999

Exit status:

0  no failing contract
1  failing warn/error/info contract, depending on --fail-on
2  invalid input, contract, or argument

BUILD
make
make test

EMBEDDING
Compile with -DDWELL_NO_MAIN and include dwell.h from a C or C++ test harness.

